Info.Name: Fledgling's Hammer
Info.Desc: A hammer for practice. Beginners will use it.

Info.Name: Bronze Hammer
Info.Desc: An easy-to-use copper hammer. For proper forging, it's still a bit unqualified.

Info.Name: Iron Hammer
Info.Desc: A strong hammer made of iron. It's just right for when you first come to the fore.

Info.Name: Silver Hammer
Info.Desc: A slender hammer made of silver. You need to master some techniques to use it flexibly.

Info.Name: Gold Hammer
Info.Desc: A luxurious hammer made of gold. An ID for many Blacksmiths.

Info.Name: Super Hammer
Info.Desc: A very balanced hammer adjusted in all aspects. It fits perfectly in your hand.

Info.Name: Flame Hammer
Info.Desc: A hammer containing Fire power. You will become enthusiastic using it.

Info.Name: Rockcrusher Hammer
Info.Desc: A barbed hammer. The difficulty is in how to make good use of the barbs.

Info.Name: Spark Hammer
Info.Desc: A hammer containing the power of thunder. The works it makes are full of shocking power.

Info.Name: Spirit Hammer
Info.Desc: An ultra hammer containing the soul of a Blacksmith. Thoroughly tempered with one heart and one mind.

Info.Name: Fluffkin Hammer
Info.Desc: The hammer that cast the sword of an ancient hero. Legendary names always come with the legendary items of the Fluffkins.

Info.Name: Clockwork Hammer
Info.Desc: A hammer that can reduce impact at regular intervals. Can stimulate the user's potential abilities.

Info.Name: Star Smasher
Info.Desc: A hammer harder than any material. It can process any material.

Info.Name: Worn Axe
Info.Desc: A practice axe abandoned by your predecessors. You can still vaguely make out the words written on it.

Info.Name: Oak Axe
Info.Desc: An axe with an oak wood handle. It's not quite suitable for real woodcutting.

Info.Name: Pine Axe
Info.Desc: An axe with a pine wood handle. Use it with care.

Info.Name: Palm Axe
Info.Desc: A shiny axe with a palm wood handle. It can't be obtained from the goddess in the lake.

Info.Name: Sugar Axe
Info.Desc: A golden axe with a sugar wood handle. It can't be obtained from the goddess in the lake.

Info.Name: Sparkle Axe
Info.Desc: An axe with a shining glow. It's made of metal that will not rust.

PassiveProperties.Name: Sacred Wind Tree Buster
PassiveProperties.Desc: Increases damage to Sacred Wind Trees

PassiveProperties.Name: Sacred Wind Tree Buster
PassiveProperties.Desc: Increases damage to Sacred Wind Trees

Info.Name: Marine Axe
Info.Desc: An axe with the aura of the sea god. It's very useful.

Info.Name: Giant's Axe
Info.Desc: An axe containing power of divine giants. It has a unique usage.

Info.Name: Goddess's Axe
Info.Desc: An axe blessed by the goddess. It's very handy.

Info.Name: Great Forest Axe
Info.Desc: An axe that can blend in with the forest. There are even rumors that there's no tree it can't cut.

Info.Name: Fluffkin Axe
Info.Desc: An axe made using techniques handed down from ancient times. Contains the Fluffkins' power.

Info.Name: Cutterfly
Info.Desc: An axe as light as a flutter. Although it looks cute, its power cannot be underestimated.

Info.Name: Meteor Axe
Info.Desc: The strongest axe. You can sense a divine power. It can even break meteors in one fell swoop.

Info.Name: Beginner's Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe used for practice. Its strength is reasonable.

Info.Name: Bronze Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A handy pickaxe made of copper. It's suitable for mining more fragile deposits.

Info.Name: Iron Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A more proper pickaxe made of iron. As long as you carefully mine, you will always gain something.

Info.Name: Silver Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A slender pickaxe made of silver. It's good for showing artistic mining techniques.

Info.Name: Gold Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A luxurious pickaxe made of gold. Obviously a higher grade than the average pickaxe.

Info.Name: Lava Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe containing the power of lava. It can echo the earth.

Info.Name: Deep Sea Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe containing the power of the deep sea. It can give ore deposits a wave-like excavation.

Info.Name: Ancient Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe containing ancient power. Time can disintegrate everything.

PassiveProperties.Name: Palm of Titan Buster
PassiveProperties.Desc: Significantly increases damage to Palms of Titan

PassiveProperties.Name: Palm of Titan Buster
PassiveProperties.Desc: Significantly increases damage to Palms of Titan

Info.Name: Mole Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe containing the power of the Moleys. With it, mining is a pleasure.

Info.Name: Solar Pickaxe
Info.Desc: The best pickaxe that received the blessing of the sun. It's the pride of Miners.

Info.Name: Fluffkin Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe held by an ancient hero. Contains the Fluffkins' power.

Info.Name: Demonic Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A Shadow pickaxe that can destroy everything. It can confuse the wielder's heart.

Info.Name: Spirit Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe that gods love to use. Even the ore it mines seems to be happy.

Info.Name: Makeshift Saw
Info.Desc: A saw for practice. It's a bit rusty.

Info.Name: Oak Saw
Info.Desc: A saw with an oak wood handle. For novices.

Info.Name: Pine Saw
Info.Desc: A saw with a pine wood handle. It's very handy.

Info.Name: Palm Saw
Info.Desc: A saw with a palm wood handle. The kind that many people love to use.

Info.Name: Sugar Saw
Info.Desc: A saw with a sugar wood handle. Uneven force is no problem.

Info.Name: Royal Saw
Info.Desc: A saw passed down from generation to generation by the Castele royal family. It's said to have been used for the renovation of the castle.

Info.Name: Sea Saw
Info.Desc: A saw used by a shipwright. It's competent for important tasks that are critical to the lives of seafarers.

Info.Name: Gold Saw
Info.Desc: A glittering saw made of pure gold. The more sophisticated the user's skills, the more this saw shines.

Info.Name: Ancient Saw
Info.Desc: A saw made of materials from dinosaurs. You can feel the vitality of dinosaurs.

Info.Name: Master Saw
Info.Desc: A saw handed down from generation to generation of master craftsmen. It seems to incorporate the superb skills of generations of famous woodworkers.

Info.Name: Fluffkin Saw
Info.Desc: A saw made using techniques handed down from ancient times. Contains the Fluffkins' power.

Info.Name: Plume Saw
Info.Desc: A saw with a divine aura sealed within. It lets you cut at a godlike speed.

Info.Name: Solar Saw
Info.Desc: A saw containing the power of the sun. Just holding it in your hand can instantly dispel the haze in your heart.

Info.Name: Guppy Rod
Info.Desc: A fishing rod for practice. It's just a small fry in the fishing industry.

Info.Name: Oak Rod
Info.Desc: A rather weak fishing rod made of oak wood. Suitable for beginners to use.

Info.Name: Pine Rod
Info.Desc: A strong fishing rod made of pine wood, with which you can catch some fish even if your skills are poor.

Info.Name: Palm Rod
Info.Desc: A tough fishing rod made of palm wood. Using it flexibly requires some skill.

Info.Name: Sugar Rod
Info.Desc: A high-quality fishing rod made of sugar wood. You can easily fish regardless of the waters.

Info.Name: Famous Fisherman's Rod
Info.Desc: A fishing rod specially customized for celebrity Anglers. All Anglers want one.

Info.Name: Sandstorm Rod
Info.Desc: It's said that this magic fishing rod can attract small sandstorms that conceal the Anglers.

PassiveProperties.Desc: Significantly increases damage to Bass of Darkness

Info.Name: Whirlpool Rod
Info.Desc: A fishing rod that claims to be able to catch fish in whirlpools. Its stability against the waves is very high.

Info.Name: Sea Cloud Rod
Info.Desc: A fishing rod specially adapted to the fishing environment of Levitania. Be one with the sky.

Info.Name: Marine Rod
Info.Desc: According to legend, it's the same fishing rod used by the god of sea. There is no fish it can't catch.

Info.Name: Fluffkin Fishing Rod
Info.Desc: A fishing rod made using techniques handed down from ancient times. Contains the Fluffkins' power.

Info.Name: Victory Fishing Rod
Info.Desc: A fishing rod that brings glory to Anglers. Holding it's a symbol of honorable status.

Info.Name: Star Fishing Rod
Info.Desc: The gods also praise this as the highest-grade fishing rod. Even meteors falling into the sea can be caught.

Info.Name: Experimental Flask
Info.Desc: A flask for practice. Cannot be used for hazardous purposes.

Info.Name: Science Flask
Info.Desc: A flask with less alkali hazard. Suitable for beginners to use.

Info.Name: Inventor's Flask
Info.Desc: A pungent flask. Use it if you want a big success.

Info.Name: Bubbling Flask
Info.Desc: A bubbling flask. What new discoveries will be made?

Info.Name: Wisdom Flask
Info.Desc: A strange flask with white smoke coming out from time to time. It makes your eyes a bit uncomfortable.

Info.Name: Sol Flask
Info.Desc: A flask containing the power of Fire. It makes you feel enthusiastic.

Info.Name: Icicle Flask
Info.Desc: A flask containing the power of ice. It makes you feel calmer.

Info.Name: Bolt Flask
Info.Desc: A flask containing the power of thunder. Inspiration gushes out all at once.

Info.Name: Forbidden Flask
Info.Desc: A flask that is prohibited from being made or possessed. Only select Alchemists can use it.

Info.Name: Miracle Flask
Info.Desc: A flask for top Alchemists. There is nothing it can't do.

Info.Name: Flask of Dawn
Info.Desc: A flask that condenses the wisdom of the ancients. It turns a long history into a creative force.

Info.Name: Big Bang Flask
Info.Desc: A flask full of huge energy. Improper use may bring disaster to the universe.

Info.Name: Yggdrasil Flask
Info.Desc: It's said that this top-tier flask can create a new world. Filled with the brilliance of life.

Info.Name: Training Needle
Info.Desc: A needle for practice. Suitable for novices who have just learned to sew.

Info.Name: Bronze Needle
Info.Desc: A copper needle suitable for novices. It's not quite durable enough for veterans.

Info.Name: Iron Needle
Info.Desc: A strong iron needle. Can easily handle thicker fabrics.

Info.Name: Silver Needle
Info.Desc: A beautiful needle made of silver. Can freely glide through the fabric.

Info.Name: Gold Needle
Info.Desc: A shiny golden needle. Meticulous sewing skills can be fully utilized with it.

Info.Name: Fashionista's Needle
Info.Desc: A needle designed for people with excellent craftsmanship and taste. It's thin but very strong.

Info.Name: New Wave Needle
Info.Desc: A needle designed with a novel idea. It's easy to use after getting used to it.

Info.Name: Gothic Needle
Info.Desc: A needle with a grudge against humans. Treating it with a warm heart will significantly improve its performance.

Info.Name: Haute Needle
Info.Desc: A needle used to sew brand name fabrics. Suitable for all kinds of fabrics.

Info.Name: Vogue Needle
Info.Desc: A needle for the best of Tailors. Those who can use it freely can be ranked among the top Tailors.

Info.Name: Vintage Needle
Info.Desc: It has sewn the stitches in ancient heroes' clothes. People who use it can regain a pure heart.

Info.Name: Death Needle
Info.Desc: The top needle that can penetrate any material, no matter how hard. It matches the dark design very well.

Info.Name: Zeus Needle
Info.Desc: Legend has it that this needle was used to sew the clothes of the gods. A needle that seems to know your designs and style.

Info.Name: Toy Frying Pan
Info.Desc: A frying pan for practice. In the eyes of first-class chefs, it's only a tool for playing house.

Info.Name: Bronze Frying Pan
Info.Desc: A copper pot that is relatively convenient to use. You can't show superb cooking skills with it.

Info.Name: Iron Frying Pan
Info.Desc: A strong iron pot. Can make a variety of delicious dishes.

Info.Name: Silver Frying Pan
Info.Desc: A silver pot that radiates brilliance. The antiseptic effect of silver makes cooking more delicious.

Info.Name: Gold Frying Pan
Info.Desc: A pot made of gold. It has excellent thermal conductivity and even heat distribution.

Info.Name: Venus Frying Pan
Info.Desc: A stylish pot decorated with seashells. It can keep the heat at a certain level.

PassiveProperties.Name: Grilled Fish Master

Info.Name: Foreign Frying Pan

Info.Name: Frymaster 2000
Info.Desc: A pot that can be used to make dishes that the gods enjoy. No matter what kind of cooking, it can be done flawlessly.

Info.Name: Ancient Frying Pan
Info.Desc: A special pot made of ancient stone. It conveys the ancient people's concept of cooking.

Info.Name: Phoenix Frying Pan
Info.Desc: A pot that is very resistant to heat. It can transform fire into the right temperature.

Info.Name: Pan de Cuisine
Info.Desc: A pot exclusively for the top chefs. It can maximize the taste of ingredients.

Info.Name: Great Hammer
Info.Desc: A hammer that can achieve the effect of a dragon's stomp with a single blow.

Info.Name: Smoked Silver
Info.Desc: A hammer that has been infused with a large amount of iron ashes and smoke from generation to generation.

Info.Name: Storm Hammer
Info.Desc: A hammer that can summon a storm with just a light swing. Each slam of the hammer makes sparks fly.

Info.Name: Shinra's Gold Hammer

Info.Name: Shin/Shinra's Gold Hammer
Info.Desc: A hammer blessed by the earth. The decoration on top makes it look like a handicraft.

Info.Name: Bear Grinder

Info.Desc: An axe that can easily cut down superior oak trees. Taste the apple at the top,  and you'll discover it's sweet.

Info.Name: Squirrel Axe
Info.Desc: An axe made in the shape of a cute squirrel. Young Woodcutters use it to  gather fruits from the trees.

Info.Name: Snow Blossom Axe
Info.Desc: The flowers on it grant the wielder the blessings of the earth. Can elegantly cut down Westwoods that are harder than stone.

Info.Name: Blossom Axe
Info.Desc: An axe that makes people smell a floral scent. Relax your shoulders and swing for an ideal strike.

Info.Name: Waterfowl Axe
Info.Desc: An axe that makes the birds sing alongside the Woodcutter and focuses on places other than practicality. It makes people feel full of energy.

Info.Name: Landfall Axe
Info.Desc: An axe whose former owner is said to have changed the landscape of Mt Snowpeak. It's best for felling pine trees.

Info.Name: Kindness Axe
Info.Desc: An axe whose former owner has given all their love to the forest. The trees it fells can't help but feel joyful.

Info.Name: Fire Axe
Info.Desc: An axe that emits the call of a Fire Dragon. It's best for felling Earth Trees.

Info.Name: Glider's Axe
Info.Desc: An axe that reminds people of Port Puerto winds. The wind can further accelerate its swings.

Info.Name: Axe of Gratitude
Info.Desc: A masterpiece made by a talented Carpenter as a thank-you for a Woodcutter. It emits a heat that encourages the wielder.

Info.Name: Xmas Eve Axe
Info.Desc: An axe that symbolizes the Holy Night. The blade is somewhat chilly.

Info.Name: Ushi-Oni Axe
Info.Desc: An axe made in the likeness of a minotaur. Though it's used for combat, its extreme sharpness makes it good for felling trees.

Info.Name: Axe of Fan
Info.Desc: An axe made in the shape of a fan. The little plum decorations are very stylish.

Info.Name: Azure Wing Axe
Info.Desc: A Wind axe that houses the power of the Wind when held tightly. The gales it makes can cut great trees in two.

Info.Name: Shin/Azure Wing Axe
Info.Desc: An axe surrounded by wind. Holding it grants one the power of Wind. With the strength of the wind, it's enough to cut down giant trees.

Info.Name: Slayer Axe/Red Cat
Info.Desc: An axe modeled after a somewhat long-winded, casual red cat.

Info.Name: Golem Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe that can deal a heavy blow like a Golem's body slam. Especially suitable for mining Iron Deposits.

Info.Name: Dragon Crush
Info.Desc: A pickaxe with dragon teeth inlaid on the top. It is effective against dragon rocks.

Info.Name: Pioneer's Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe used by the pioneers of history to build a fortified city from gravel.

Info.Name: Windlord's Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe that can converge the power of a tornado to one point and give a full blow to the deposit.

Info.Name: Mountainlord's Pickaxe
Info.Desc: The true power lying dormant in this pickaxe can only be awoken by the one who conquers the mountain and gains its approval.

Info.Name: Love Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A dazzling pickaxe, decorated with the loot of a Miner who is crazy about gemstones.

Info.Name: Haniwa Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe unearthed from Haniwa Cave. It's generally believed that it has been used to repeatedly excavate Haniwa ore deposit.

Info.Name: Crystal Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe made stronger after processing with crystals. Can easily crush natural crystals.

Info.Name: Warrior's Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A heavy, ugly pickaxe. Because of this, it's very strong and durable. It can compete with Blackiron Deposits.

Info.Name: Passionate Pickaxe
Info.Desc: As long as you have this pickaxe and a strong physique, no dream is impossible to realize. It can mine more copper.

Info.Name: Earthlord's Pickaxe
Info.Desc: A pickaxe blessed by the spirits. When you hold it, you can gain the power of the Earth and collect gale-wrapped Wingstones more efficiently.
